Description:
[recto] Bruegel. Ad [Addendum] Proverbs. Important article by Gisela Zick, 'Der zerbrochene Krug als Bildmotiv des 18. Jahrhunderts', in: Wallraf-Richartz-Jahrbuch, XXXI, 1969, pp.149 ff. Here reference to a XVc. MS of Proverbs with illustrations:
Grace Frank & Dorothy Miner, Proverbes en rimes. Text and illustrations of the fifteenth century from a French manuscript in the Walters Art Gallery, Baltimore, Baltimore [The Johns Hopkins Press], 1937;
Otto Ernst Moll, Sprichwörter-Bibliographie, Frankfurt am Main [Klostermann], 1958;
[verso] Grace Frank, 'Proverbes en rimes', Romanic Review, 31,1940, pp. 209-238;
Other illustrated Proverbs MSS. around 1500, Paris, Bibl.Nat., MS.fr. 24461, Chantilly Musée MS. 509; London, Br.Mus. Add MS. 17277; Paris, Bibl. d'Arsenal, MS 5066; see also p. 191 note 3, p. 152 Repr. of Proverbes Flamands (detail) by Sebastian Vrancx, Brussels Musée see Grauls, Bulletin Mus.Royaux 9, 1960; Samuel Singer, Sprichwörter des Mittelalters, 3 vols., Bern [Lang], 1944-1947. see [Jan] Grauls, [= Het spreekwoordenschilderij van Sebastiaan Vrancx], Bulletin Mus. Royaux 9, 1960 [3-4, pp. 107-164].
